analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Market equilibrium persists amid rising volatility. The GMS baseline at 50 mandates a pivot to tactical neutrality as systemic volatility expands, evidenced by the 5% escalation in the VIX. While domestic equities maintain nominal appreciation, the degradation of the global-macro vector and flat inflation proxies signal a deceleration in the fiscal-monetary nexus. Liquidity convexity is diminishing, and the idiosyncratic divergence in emerging markets necessitates risk-mitigation. Aggressive capital deployment must cease to preserve core solvency. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
